### alert(): not even once

`alert(value);` pops up a browser-level modal containing `value`. It‚Äôs often the first debugging method taught to JS newbies; it‚Äôs concise, easy to understand, and provides immediate feedback. Unfortunately, **it‚Äôs a terrible debugging utility and you shouldn‚Äôt use it**.

